      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To differentiate between administrative error, theft, and other causes, consider a multi-step approach. First, use statistical analysis to determine if the discrepancy is an outlier, and then implement root cause analysis (RCA) to identify sources. This might include reviewing inventory turnovers, employee performance data, and job responsibilities to pinpoint potential weaknesses. You can also conduct observation interviews with employees and analyze paperwork to identify if administrative issues, such as incorrect labeling or data entry errors, are to blame.",
